    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mushroom-and-thyme-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the onion is cooking, slice your <strong>flat white mushrooms</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mushroom-and-thyme-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the<strong> sliced mushrooms</strong> and cook for 8-10 min further or until the mushrooms are beginning to caramelise</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mushroom-and-thyme-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the cooked pasta and then return to the pot</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mushroom-and-thyme-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pasta is cooking, strip your<strong> thyme leaves </strong>from their stems and chop them finely, discard the stems</p><p>Tip: Hold the top of the herb sprigs firmly and slide your fingers down their lengths to easily remove the leaves</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mushroom-and-thyme-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mushrooms have caramelised, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>thyme</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further</p><p>Add your <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> and <strong>vegetable stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mushroom-and-thyme-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pine kernel & seed mix</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until lightly toasted</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Remove the mushroom pan from the heat and stir in your <strong>cultured coconut</strong>, then add the <strong>drained pasta </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> mushroom & thyme pasta</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mushroom-and-thyme-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>mushroom & thyme tortiglioni</strong> and season with a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>toasted pine kernel & seed mix</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
